 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46329"><img src="http://www.thepalecourt.com/signaturevara.jpg"><BR>60 Iksar Grandmaster<a> </a><a>Celestial Fist - Whistling Fist of Thule </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utheodwynriddermark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheodwynRiddermark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 377<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/10/02 1:03:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3708.topic&index=122>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiliara</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Usually when pulling we are getting hit in the back. Avoidance does NOTHING when hit from behind. Pulling just got a LOT harder.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'd argue that this shouldn't happen.  We should pull mobs walking backward wherever possible.  That's where all the skill comes in.  Watching a mob path, navigating your turns, knowing your distances, etc.<br>
<br>
That's what makes a mob fun.  You have to stare down the gullet of a mob as you walk backward to your raid in order to control its pathing and its capacity to aggro mobs.<br>
<br>
I can't tell you how many times I've seen a monk go out, throw a fishbone dart or shuriken, turn tail, run back, the mob takes the long path around, brings 4 more mobs, and then says &quot;WTF?  Where did those come from?&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, this is the province of the monk who runs out, ticks off a mob, runs back, FD's at the raid, says &quot;Heal me&quot;, and watches their raid get swamped and killed.<br>
<br>
Running with the mob chasing you hitting you in the back is a warrior pull, not a monk pull.  We're about finesse and tactics, because we don't have the HP to be otherwise.  How smart or hard is it to chuck a thing, turn around, and scream &quot;Get it off meeeeeeeeee!&quot;<br>
<br>
Not hard.  Rather boring.<br>
<br>
A good monk is a smart monk.  I don't mind if it's hard.  I mind if its statistically improbable, which is my issue with the nerf.<br>
<br>
Theo<br>
<br>
